; NAME: Lose Coins by Turn (test)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct

ADDIU SP SP -48
SW RA 44(SP)
SW S0 40(SP)
SW S1 36(SP)
SW S2 32(SP)

SW R0 20(SP) ; A4
SW R0 24(SP) ; A5
SW R0 28(SP) ; A6
ADDI A0 R0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
; Visit the following link to get the full list of Character Images
; https://github.com/PartyPlanner64/PartyPlanner64/wiki/Displaying-Messages

; The rest here perform the "wait for confirmation"

NOP

NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

NOP

NOP

SLTI S1 S0 31

NOP

SLTI S1 S0 41

NOP

J fiftyturns
NOP

Next Space Setup.code:
; NAME: Next Space Setup
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Space|Next
; PARAM: Space|Prev

ADDIU SP SP -40
SW RA 36(SP)

LI A0 -1 ; Assigns Current Player Index to A0
ADDIU A1 R0 Next_chain_index ; Assigns Chain Index to A1
JAL SetNextChainAndSpace
ADDIU A2 R0 Next_chain_space_index ; Assigns Space Index to A2

LI A0 -1
ADDIU A1 R0 Prev_chain_index
JAL SetPrevChainAndSpace
ADDIU A2 R0 Prev_chain_space_index

LW RA 36(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 40

Sneeze Warp v4.code:
; NAME: Sneeze Warp v4
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Space|Destination
; PARAM: Space|PrevSpace
; PARAM: Space|Space

ADDIU SP SP -80 ; Aligned by 8 to avoid N64 crash
SW RA 76(SP)
SW S0 72(SP)
SW S1 68(SP)
SW S2 64(SP)
SW S3 60(SP)
SW S4 56(SP)
SW S5 52(SP)
SW S6 48(SP)
SW S7 44(SP)

; S0 = Flag for Warp 
; S1 = Message Pointer
; S2 = Destination Chain Index
; S3 = Destination Space Index
; S5 = True Space Index
; S4 = Current Player's Index
; S6 = Previous Chain Index - X Coords
; S7 = Previous Space Index - Y Coords

LUI S1 hi(Message)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(Message)
LI S2 Destination_chain_index
LI S3 Destination_chain_space_index
LI S6 PrevSpace_chain_index
LI S7 PrevSpace_chain_space_index

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
MOVE A1 S1 ; Copy Message Pointer to A1
LI A2 0 ; Param 2
JAL ShowMessage
LI A3 0 ; Param 3

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL CloseMessage
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

LI A0 4 ; Standard Warp
JAL InitFadeOut
LI A1 16 ; 16 Frames

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 17 ; 17 Frames

JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex ; Player Index located at V0
NOP
MOVE S4 V0

JAL GetPlayerStruct
LI A0 -1

LBU T0 3(V0)
JAL PlaySound
ADDIU A0 T0 0x287 ; Play sad voice

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x197 ; Flying Snowball sound

; WARP --------------------------------------------------------------
MOVE A0 S4 ; Current Player Index to A0
MOVE A1 S2 ; Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPlayerOntoChain
MOVE A2 S3 ; Space Index to A2

MOVE A0 S4 ; Current Player Index to A0
MOVE A1 S6 ; Chain Index to A1
JAL SetPrevChainAndSpace
MOVE A2 S7 ; Space Index to A2

MOVE A0 S2 ; Destination Chain Index
JAL GetAbsSpaceIndexFromChainSpaceIndex ; True Space Index at V0
MOVE A1 S3 ; Destination Space Index

MOVE S5 V0 ; Copy True Space Index to S5

MOVE A0 S5 ; Copy True Space Index to A0
JAL SetSpaceType 
LI A1 4 ; Happening Space value 

JAL GetSpaceData ; Pointer to Space Data at V0
MOVE A0 S5

ADDIU V0 V0 8 ; This gets the X pos of the space
LW V1 0(V0) 
MOVE S6 V1 ; Copy to S6

ADDIU V0 V0 8 ; This gets the Y pos of the space
LW V1 0(V0)
MOVE T1 V1 ; Copy to T1

LI T2 0x41200000 ; Float value for 10?
MTC1 T2 F2 ; Move Float to F1?
MTC1 T1 F4 ; Move Space Y Pos float to F1?
ADD.S F6 F2 F4 ; Add the floats for maximum floatiness
MFC1 S7 F6 ; Move total to T1?

JAL GetPlayerStruct ; Player Struct at V0
LI A0 -1 ; Current Player

LW V1 0x24(V0) ; Load Offset 24 into V1
ADDIU V1 V1 0xC ; Add 0xC to get current player's X Coords
SW S6 0(V1) 

ADDIU V1 V1 8 ; This should load current player's Y Coords
SW S7 0(V1)
; WARP --------------------------------------------------------------
LI A0 -1 ; Current Player's Index
LI A1 1 ; Frames it takes to turn
JAL 0x800ED20C ; RotatePlayerModel
LI A2 Space ; Space Index to face towards

LI A0 -1 ; Current Player
LI A1 4 ; Dizzy animation
JAL SetBoardPlayerAnimation
LI A2 2 ; Loop

JAL SleepProcess ; Sleeps for 35 frames
LI A0 35

LI A0 4 ; Standard Warp
JAL InitFadeIn
LI A1 16 ; 16 Frames

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 29 ; 29 Frames

JAL DeactivateHiddenBlocks
MOVE A0 S5 ; Pass True Space Index to A0

exit:
LW RA 76(SP)
LW S0 72(SP)
LW S1 68(SP)
LW S2 64(SP)
LW S3 60(SP)
LW S4 56(SP)
LW S5 52(SP)
LW S6 48(SP)
LW S7 44(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 80

DeactivateHiddenBlocks:
; A0 = True Space Index 
ADDIU SP SP -32
SW RA 28(SP)

LUI T1 hi(hidden_block_star_space_index)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(hidden_block_star_space_index)
LB T0 0(T1) ; Load Value of Star HB Address to T0
BEQ T0 A0 movestarHB
NOP
LUI T1 hi(hidden_block_coins_space_index)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(hidden_block_coins_space_index)
LB T0 0(T1) ; Load Value of Coin HB Address to T0
BEQ T0 A0 movecoinsHB
NOP
LUI T1 hi(hidden_block_item_space_index)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(hidden_block_item_space_index)
LB T0 0(T1) ; Load Value of Item HB Address to T0
BEQ T0 A0 moveitemHB
NOP
J DeactivateHiddenBlocks_exit
NOP

movestarHB:
LUI T2 hi(0x800CD096)
ADDIU T2 T2 lo(0x800CD096) ; Load Free RAM Address to T2
SB T0 0(T2) ; Store HB's True Space Index 
LI T0 0xFF
SB T0 0(T1) ; Removes HB from the Star HB Address
J DeactivateHiddenBlocks_exit
NOP

movecoinsHB:
LUI T2 hi(0x800CD097)
ADDIU T2 T2 lo(0x800CD097) ; Load Free RAM Address to T2
SB T0 0(T2) ; Store HB's True Space Index 
LI T0 0xFF
SB T0 0(T1) ; Removes HB from the Coins HB Address
J DeactivateHiddenBlocks_exit
NOP

moveitemHB:
LUI T2 hi(0x800CD098)
ADDIU T2 T2 lo(0x800CD098) ; Load Free RAM Address to T2
SB T0 0(T2) ; Store HB's True Space Index 
LI T0 0xFF
SB T0 0(T1) ; Removes HB from the Item HB Address

DeactivateHiddenBlocks_exit:
LW RA 28(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 32


.align 16
Message:
.ascii "Ah"
.byte 0x3D
.ascii "CHOOO"
.byte 0xC2
.ascii " You sneezed yourself to another space"
.byte 0xC2 ; Exclamation Mark (!)
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause (THIS ALWAYS GOES AT THE END)

Daisy's Mirror v4.code:
; NAME: Daisy's Mirror v4
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Number|Coins
; PARAM: Space|SpaceToFace

; This code is designed to give the landing or passing player an item
; of your choice. If they have no space to carry the item, they will
; receive coins. The number of coins is given by the parameter Coins.

ADDIU SP SP -40
SW RA 36(SP)
SW S0 32(SP)

; S0 = Current Player Struct / Current Player Index

;===Set Idle Animation===
LI A0 -1 ; Set current player
LI A1 -1 ; Set idle animation
JAL SetBoardPlayerAnimation
LI A2 2 ; Loop the animation

;===Rotate Player Towards Space===
LI A0 -1 ; Set current player
LI A1 8 ; Take 8 frames to rotate
JAL 0x800ED20C ; Rotate player func
LI A2 SpaceToFace ; Face towards SpaceToFace

;===Check Player Item Slots===
JAL GetPlayerStruct
LI A0 -1 ; Get current player struct

MOVE S0 V0
LI T2 0 ; Loop counter
checkslots:
LI T1 0xFF ; No item value
LBU T0 0x18(S0) ; Load item 1 from offset of player struct
BEQ T0 T1 getitem
ADDIU T2 T2 1
LI T1 3
BEQ T2 T1 getcoins
ADDIU S0 S0 1
J checkslots
NOP

;===Get Coins Message===
getcoins:
LUI A1 hi(CoinsMessage)
JAL CallMessage
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(CoinsMessage)

;===Get Coins===
JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex
NOP
MOVE S0 V0

MOVE A0 S0
JAL AdjustPlayerCoinsGradual
LI A1 Coins ; Give current player Coins

MOVE A0 S0
JAL ShowPlayerCoinChange
LI A1 Coins ; Show coin change HUD

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 30 ; Wait 30 frames

J exit
NOP

;===Get Item Message===
getitem:
LUI A1 hi(ItemMessage)
JAL CallMessage
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(ItemMessage)

;===Give Item===
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x112 ; Turn Start Sound Index
; Use the Audio Player on PP64 to find other sound indexes to use
; Then use the following link to know what Sound Index you need
; https://pastebin.com/H1jxNFqr

LI T0 0x10 ; T0 contains Barter Box
SB T0 0x18(S0) ; Place item on last-checked item slot

; 0x00 = Mushroom
; 0x01 = Skeleton Key
; 0x02 = Poison Mushroom
; 0x03 = Reverse Mushroom
; 0x04 = Cellular Shopper
; 0x05 = Warp Block
; 0x06 = Plunder Chest
; 0x07 = Bowser Phone
; 0x08 = Dueling Glove
; 0x09 = Lucky Lamp
; 0x0A = Golden Mushroom
; 0x0B = Boo Bell
; 0x0C = Boo Repellant
; 0x0D = Bowser Suit
; 0x0E = Magic Lamp
; 0x0F = Koopa Card
; 0x10 = Barter Box
; 0x11 = Lucky Coin
; 0x12 = Wacky Watch

exit:
;===Play Happy Voice===
JAL GetPlayerStruct
LI A0 -1 ; Get current player struct

LBU T0 3(V0) ; Load character value from offset of player struct
JAL PlaySound
ADDIU A0 T0 0x2BE ; Add character value to Mario's happy voice
; Character voices are their "character value" distance away from
; Mario's, e.g. Luigi's character value = 1, so Luigi's happy voice
; is 1 away from Mario's.
; 0x2BE = Happy Voice, 0x287 = Sad Voice

;===Play Happy Animation===
LI A0 -1 ; Set current player
LI A1 5 ; Set happy animation
JAL SetBoardPlayerAnimation
LI A2 0 ; Do not loop animation

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 40 ; Wait 40 frames to play animation

LW S0 32(SP)
LW RA 36(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 40

.align 4
;===Mini Func to Call Message===
CallMessage:
ADDIU SP SP -32
SW RA 28(SP)

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
; Visit the following link to get the full list of Character Images
; https://github.com/PartyPlanner64/PartyPlanner64/wiki/Displaying-Messages
; If you use a character image, check the bottom of the code
LI A2 0
JAL ShowMessage
LI A3 0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL CloseMessage
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

LW RA 28(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 32

HB Fix.code:
; NAME: HB Fix
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct

ADDIU SP SP -40
SW RA 36(SP)

LUI T1 hi(0x800CD096)
ADDIU T1 T1 lo(0x800CD096) ; Load Star HB RAM Reserved Space Address
LB T0 0(T1) ; Load Value of Address to T0
BNE T0 R0 putStarHBback
NOP
ADDIU T1 T1 1 ; Load Coins HB RAM Reserved Space Address
LB T0 0(T1)
BNE T0 R0 putCoinsHBback
NOP
ADDIU T1 T1 1 ; Load Item HB RAM Reserved Space Address
LB T0 0(T1)
BNE T0 R0 putItemHBback
NOP
J exit
NOP

putStarHBback:
LUI T2 hi(hidden_block_star_space_index)
ADDIU T2 T2 lo(hidden_block_star_space_index)
SB T0 0(T2) ; Store HB back in its address
SB R0 0(T1) ; Remove HB from RAM Reserved Space
J exit
NOP

putCoinsHBback:
LUI T2 hi(hidden_block_coins_space_index)
ADDIU T2 T2 lo(hidden_block_coins_space_index)
SB T0 0(T2) ; Store HB back in its address
SB R0 0(T1) ; Remove HB from RAM Reserved Space
J exit
NOP

putItemHBback:
LUI T2 hi(hidden_block_item_space_index)
ADDIU T2 T2 lo(hidden_block_item_space_index)
SB T0 0(T2) ; Store HB back in its address
SB R0 0(T1) ; Remove HB from RAM Reserved Space
J exit
NOP

JR RA

; NAME: Picnic Basket v4

; PARAM: Space|CurrentSpace

SW RA 44(SP)
SW S0 40(SP)
SW S1 36(SP)
SW S2 32(SP)

; S0 = Current Player Struct
; S1 = Message
; S2 = Exit Flag

LI S2 0

LI A0 -1
LI A1 -1
JAL SetBoardPlayerAnimation
LI A2 2

JAL GetPlayerStruct
LI A0 -1

MOVE S0 V0
LBU T0 0xE(S0) ; Player stars at T0
LI T1 99
BEQ T0 T1 TooManyStars
NOP

LUI S1 hi(GetStarMessage)
J displaymessage
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(GetStarMessage)

TooManyStars:
LUI S1 hi(NoStarMessage)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(NoStarMessage)
LI S2 1

displaymessage:
SW R0 16(SP)
SW R0 20(SP)
SW R0 24(SP)
LI A0 -1
MOVE A1 S1
LI A2 0
JAL ShowMessage
LI A3 0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL CloseMessage
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

BNEZ S2 exit
NOP

LB T0 0xE(S0)
ADDIU T0 T0 1
SB T0 0xE(S0)

LI A0 -1
LI A1 1
JAL 0x800ED20C
LI A2 CurrentSpace

JAL PlayMusic
LI A0 111

LI A0 -1
LI A1 6
JAL SetBoardPlayerAnimation
LI A2 0

LBU T0 3(S0)
JAL PlaySound
ADDIU A0 T0 0x263

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 110

JAL GetBoardAudioIndex
NOP

JAL PlayMusic
MOVE A0 V0

exit:
LW S0 40(SP)
LW S1 36(SP)
LW S2 32(SP)
LW RA 44(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 48

.align 16
GetStarMessage:
.ascii "How wonderful"
.byte 0xC2
.byte 0x0A
.ascii "There was a"
.byte 0x07 ; Yellow Font
.ascii " Star"
.byte 0x08 ; White Font
.ascii " in the picnic basket"
.byte 0xC2 ; Exclamation Mark (!)
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause

.align 16
NoStarMessage:
.ascii "How unfortunate"
.byte 0xC2
.byte 0x0A
.ascii "There was"
.byte 0x03 ; Yellow Font
.ascii " no Star"
.byte 0x08 ; White Font
.ascii " in the picnic basket"
.byte 0xC2 ; Exclamation Mark (!)
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause

Piranha Plant v3.code:
; NAME: Piranha Plant v3
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct

ADDIU SP SP -48
SW RA 44(SP)
SW S0 40(SP)
SW S1 36(SP)

; S0 = Coins
; S1 = Current Player Index

LI A0 4 ; Assigns Happening fade-out
JAL InitFadeOut ; Fade to black
LI A1 16 ; Assigns 16 frames of fade-out

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 17 ; Sleep for 16 frames

JAL GetPlayerStruct
LI A0 -1

LBU T0 3(V0)
JAL PlaySound
ADDIU A0 T0 0x287 ; Mario's Despair Index

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 30 ; Sleep for 30 frames

LI A0 -1 ; Player Index (Current Player)
LI A1 4 ; Animation Index (Dizzy)
JAL SetBoardPlayerAnimation
LI A2 2

LI A0 4 ; Assigns Happening fade-in
JAL InitFadeIn
LI A1 16 ; Assigns 16 frames of fade-in

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 17 ; Sleep for 16 frames

SW R0 16(SP) ; A4
SW R0 20(SP) ; A5
SW R0 24(SP) ; A6
LI A0 -1 ; Character image (-1 for none)
; Visit the following link to get the full list of Character Images
; https://github.com/PartyPlanner64/PartyPlanner64/wiki/Displaying-Messages
; If you use a character image, check the bottom of the code
LUI A1 hi(Message)
ADDIU A1 A1 lo(Message) ; This loads "Message" into the Textbox
LI A2 0
JAL ShowMessage
LI A3 0

; The rest here perform the "wait for confirmation"
; and probably messagebox teardown.
JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL CloseMessage
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

JAL GetRandomByte
NOP

LI T0 4
DIVU V0 T0
MFHI T1
LI T2 3
MULT T1 T2
MFLO T1
ADDIU S0 T1 4

; Give the player the coins
JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex
NOP
MOVE S1 V0
MOVE A0 S1
JAL AdjustPlayerCoinsGradual
SUBU A1 R0 S0

; Display the coin change by the player stats
MOVE A0 S1
JAL ShowPlayerCoinChange
SUBU A1 R0 S0

; Sleep for 30 frames to let coin change take effect
JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 30

LW S0 40(SP)
LW S1 36(SP)
LW RA 44(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 48

.align 16
Message:
.ascii "YOWCH"
.byte 0xC2
.ascii " You got bit by the"
.byte 0x03
.ascii " Piranha Plant"
.byte 0x08
.byte 0xC2 ; Exclamation Mark (!)
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause (THIS ALWAYS GOES AT THE END)

; Here's a list of the most common bytes you'll need
; .byte 0x01 ; Black Font
; .byte 0x03 ; Red Font
; .byte 0x04 ; Purple Font
; .byte 0x05 ; Green Font
; .byte 0x06 ; Blue font
; .byte 0x07 ; Yellow Font
; .byte 0x08 ; White Font
; .byte 0x85 ; Period (.)
; .byte 0xC2 ; Exclamation Mark (!)
; .byte 0xC3 ; Question Mark (?)
; .byte 0x82 ; Comma (,)
; .byte 0x0A ; New Line (Writes Below)
; .byte 0x5C ; Apostrophe (')
; .byte 0x29 ; Coin icon
; .byte 0x3D ; - (minus)
; .byte 0x3E ; x (multiply)
; .byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause

; If your message has an image, use this at the start of each line
; .byte 0x1A,0x1A,0x1A,0x1A ; Padding for picture

Petey Piranha v4.code:
; NAME: Petey Piranha v4
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct
; PARAM: Space|Space

ADDIU SP SP -48
SW RA 44(SP)
SW S0 40(SP)
SW S1 36(SP)
SW S2 32(SP)

; S2 = Current Player Index

LI A0 -1 ; Current Player's Index
LI A1 8 ; Frames it takes to turn
JAL 0x800ED20C ; RotatePlayerModel
LI A2 Space ; Space Index to face towards

LUI A0 hi(coinmessage)
JAL CallMessage
ADDIU A0 A0 lo(coinmessage)

JAL GetCurrentPlayerIndex
NOP
MOVE S2 V0
MOVE A0 S2
JAL PlayerHasCoins
LI A1 50
BEQZ V0 bye
NOP

; Give the player the coins
MOVE A0 S2
JAL AdjustPlayerCoinsGradual
ADDIU A1 R0 -50

; Display the coin change by the player stats
MOVE A0 S2
JAL ShowPlayerCoinChange
ADDIU A1 R0 -50

; Sleep for 30 frames to let coin change take effect
JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 30

LI A0 4
JAL InitFadeOut
LI A1 16

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 16

LI S0 0x0 ; Begin with Player 1

LUI S1 hi(p1_stars)
ADDIU S1 S1 lo(p1_stars) ; S1 is the address of Player 1's Stars

START:
LI T0 0x4 ; If all Players have been given coins, stop
BEQ S0 T0 wait
NOP

BEQ S2 S0 nextplayer ; If the current player is S0, skip them
NOP

givestar:
JAL GetPlayerStruct
MOVE A0 S0

LBU T0 3(V0)
JAL PlaySound
ADDIU A0 T0 0x287

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 15

LB T2 0(S1) ; Load Player's Star count into S2
BEQZ T2 losecoins
NOP
ADDIU T2 T2 -1 ; Add 1 to their Star count
SB T2 0(S1) ; Insert new Star count into the address

nextplayer:
ADDIU S0 S0 1 ; Add 1 to check the next Player
J START
ADDIU S1 S1 0x38 ; This makes it load the next Player's Stars

losecoins:
MOVE A0 S0
JAL AdjustPlayerCoins
ADDIU A1 R0 -15

J nextplayer
NOP

;GIVE COINS END------------------------------------------------------
wait:
JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x122 ; Star Sound Index
; Use the Audio Player on PP64 to find other sound indexes to use
; Then use the following link to know what Sound Index you need
; https://pastebin.com/H1jxNFqr

JAL SleepProcess
LI A0 20 ; Amount of frames the game waits for coin handouts

LI A0 4
JAL InitFadeIn
LI A1 16

JAL SleepProcess ; Sleeps for 30 frames
LI A0 16

LUI A0 hi(Message)
JAL CallMessage
ADDIU A0 A0 lo(Message)

J exit
NOP

bye:
LUI A0 hi(byemessage)
JAL CallMessage
ADDIU A0 A0 lo(byemessage)

exit:
LW S0 40(SP)
LW S1 36(SP)
LW S2 32(SP)
LW RA 44(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 48

.align 4
CallMessage:
ADDIU SP SP -40
SW RA 36(SP)
SW S1 32(SP)

MOVE S1 A0

JAL PlaySound
LI A0 0x4E4

SW R0 16(SP)
SW R0 20(SP)
SW R0 24(SP)
LI A0 -1
MOVE A1 S1
LI A2 0
JAL ShowMessage
LI A3 0

JAL 0x800EC9DC
NOP
JAL CloseMessage
NOP
JAL 0x800EC6EC
NOP

LW S1 32(SP)
LW RA 36(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 40

.align 16
coinmessage:
.ascii "You fool"
.byte 0xC2 ; !
.ascii " Behold the power of "
.byte 0x03
.ascii "Petey"
.byte 0x01
.byte 0xC2 ; !
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause

.align 16
Message:
.ascii "What did you think"
.byte 0xC3
.ascii " This is why"
.byte 0x0A
.ascii "you don"
.byte 0x5C
.ascii "t mess with"
.byte 0x03 ; Yellow Font
.ascii " Petey"
.byte 0x08 ; White Font
.byte 0xC2 ; Exclamation Mark (!)
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause

.align 16
byemessage:
.ascii "Actually"
.byte 0x82
.ascii " I don"
.byte 0x5C
.ascii "t feel too well"
.byte 0x85
.ascii " So"
.byte 0x82
.ascii " BEGONE"
.byte 0xC2
.byte 0xC2
.byte 0xFF,0 ; FF=Pause

Dead-End Reverse Fixup (v4).code:
; NAME: Dead-End Reverse Fixup (v4)
; GAMES: MP3_USA
; EXECUTION: Direct

ADDIU SP SP -40
SW RA 36(SP)

JAL GetPlayerStruct
LI A0 -1

LBU T0 0x17(V0) ; load player status flags
LI T1 0x81
BEQ T0 T1 change
NOP
J exit
change:
LI T1 0x80
SB T1 0x17(V0)

exit:
LW RA 36(SP)
JR RA
ADDIU SP SP 40
